"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1930219-Alistair-Jonny-Brownless-not-competing-Olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Jonny and Alistair Brownlee, two of Britain's most decorated triathletes, will not be representing Team GB at the Paris Olympics this year.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 29, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alistair Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 38, \"end\": 45, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8110466523248478, \"rank\": 0.2329625418724497, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999827196, \"rank\": 1.7347977303425102e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Yorkshire-born brothers will be absent from the 2024 Games in France, each due to different circumstances.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9312127036116371, \"rank\": 0.07380555685704815, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alistair, a two-time Olympic gold medallist, chose to retire from racing at Olympic distance after missing the Tokyo Games three years ago because of a persistent ankle injury.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0549312618792457e-40, \"text\": \"Alistair\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alistair underwent surgery on his ankle in 2015, but it started troubling him again in March 2021, necessitating further surgery to remove scar tissue around his tendons.\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Yee and Jonny represented Team GB at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, with Yee securing a silver medal and Jonny finishing fifth.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 634, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999827196, \"rank\": 1.7347977303425102e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was ultimately won by Norway's Kristian Blummenfelt, while New Zealand's Hayden Wilde took the bronze.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6750517909818096, \"rank\": 0.3691958353740683, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristian Blummenfelt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristian_Blummenfelt\"}, {\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"score\": 0.9768661264626762, \"rank\": 0.023119550436348953, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"score\": 0.9985275775758524, \"rank\": 0.0014745309163794722, \"text\": \"Wilde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now aged 36, Alistair has retired from Olympic Triathlon boasting a gold medal from both the London 2012 and Rio 2016 Olympics, as well as two championship titles from the 2014 Commonwealth Games in Glasgow in the triathlon and mixed-team relay events.\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 866, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0549312618792457e-40, \"text\": \"Alistair\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9912850865296258, \"rank\": 0.008791383294514005, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a shocking turn of events for British triathlon, Olympic hero Jonny Brownlee has been overlooked for the Paris 2024 squad in favour of up-and-coming athlete Sam Dickinson, despite Brownlee's stellar Olympic pedigree.\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonny Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.672754155022552e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"score\": 0.999985295493271, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Dickinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1290, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9991329492462092, \"rank\": 0.0007173003212877287, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 34, the decorated triathlete - who boasts an impressive collection of gold, silver, and bronze medals from previous Games - was surpassed by Sam Dickinson who outperformed him at a key event in June.\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1471, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"score\": 0.999985295493271, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Dickinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Dickinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jonny Brownlee, disheartened by the decision, took toInstagramto express his feelings: \\\"I have not been selected for the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonny Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tokyo mixed team relay was one of the many highlights of my career and I still believe I could have helped Team GB win another medal in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1684, \"end\": 1689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8457702784661818, \"rank\": 0.18235414945572312, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999827196, \"rank\": 1.7347977303425102e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987367119, \"rank\": 1.2631438147677597e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued to show his undying support for Team GB: \\\"I will be supporting the Team in whatever way I can and really hope they go on to defend the title!\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have achieved more than I could ever have imagined in my Olympic career.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After 99 world triathlon starts, 52 podiums and 3 Olympic medals, it's not the fairytale ending that I'd wished for, but Paris was always a bonus, and it can be the unwritten chapter of an incredible book!\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987367119, \"rank\": 1.2631438147677597e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have a great summer to look forward to and some exciting racing ahead.\\\"\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The younger Brownlee sibling captured the nation's heart with top finishes across three Olympic Games, including a memorable gold in Tokyo 2021's mixed relay event, partnering with Jessica Learmonth, Georgia Taylor-Brown, and Alex Yee to clinch victory in a formidable time of 1:23:41.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8457702784661818, \"rank\": 0.18235414945572312, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2521, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Learmonth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jess_Learmonth\"}, {\"begin\": 2540, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Georgia Taylor-Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Taylor-Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond his recent gold, Brownlee also took home the silver medal in Rios 2016 triathlon and snagged a bronze in London 2012, asserting his status as a true British sporting icon.\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9991329492462092, \"rank\": 0.0007173003212877287, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 2738, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999949950507, \"rank\": 5.0047269064310974e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2782, \"end\": 2789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.7201027674585633, \"rank\": 0.20478659613358174, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http: